HERITAGE BANCORP Inc., Holyoke, Mass., said it received $10 million from a private placement of a note and common stock warrant with Monarch Life Insurance Co., Springfield, Mass.
The warrant gives Monarch the right to purchase as much as 610,500 shares, or about 7.5%, of Heritage's common stock at $16.38 a share, subject to certain conditions, Heritage said.
The $10 million note matures Sept. 30, 2001.
Proceeds will be used for capital at the bank holding company's Heritage Bank for Savings unit and for general working capital, the company said. 

